29/08/2003
OHRID, Macedonia-- The international forum "Dialogue Among Civilisations" opens Friday (29 August) in Ohrid, bringing together the presidents of all Southeast European states, UNESCO Director General Koichiro Matsuura, officials from the UN, EU and other international institutions, and representatives of the international business community.
Macedonian President Boris Trajkovski will use the opportunity to hold a series of regional meetings with his counterparts.
On Thursday, Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski met with Hungarian President Ferenc Madl, who is making a three-day visit to Macedonia.
Talks focused on economic co-operation.
(A1 TV, MIA - 28/08/03)
